
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-melnikov-smtp-lang-07.txt'>
    <title>"SMTP Language Extension", Alexey Melnikov</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-melnikov-smtp-lang-07.txt</link>
    <description>The Simple Mail Transfer Protocol (RFC 2821) allows server responses to include human-readable text that in many cases needs to be presented to the user. This document specifies a way for a client to negotiate which language the server should use when sending human-readable text. It also extends the UTF-8 Delivery Status Notifications format to include language field for the human-readable text.</description>
    <dc:date>2007-06-18T22:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
